article.description: East Carolina holds on late to defeat Houston 66-61
article.headline: East Carolina holds on late to defeat Houston 66-61
article.linkText: East Carolina holds on late to defeat Houston 66-61
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. -- B.J. Tyson scored 16 points and Caleb White added 14 as East Carolina secured its first American Athletic Conference victory, 66-61 over Houston on Wednesday night. As the teams scrapped down to the wire, the Pirates (8-9, 1-3) made 5 of their last 7 shots from the field starting with Marshall Guilmette's first-ever 3-pointer to put East Carolina up 52-48. Terry Whisnant followed with a trey to make it 52-51, answering a long-range dagger from Houston's Cavon Baker. White added a layup and a jumper and Tyson dunked after a Whisnant steal, putting the Pirates up 61-56 with 96 seconds left to play. Baker added another trey for Houston (7-9, 0-5) but the Pirates closed it out at the line, making 5 of 7 foul shots. Whisnant finished with 13 points for East Carolina, which made 24 of 54 shots. Danrad Knowles scored 16 for Houston, L.J. Rose 15.
